LeetCode 22 – Generate Parentheses

Problem:
Given an integer n, generate all combinations of well-formed parentheses consisting of n pairs of parentheses.

Example:
Input: n = 3
Output:
((()))
(()())
(())()
()(())
()()()

Concept:
Use recursion and backtracking to build the parentheses string step by step.

We keep track of:
open  → number of '(' used
close → number of ')' used

Rules:
1. We can add '(' if open < n
   (because we cannot exceed n opening brackets)

2. We can add ')' if close < open
   (because we cannot close more brackets than we opened)

Base Condition:
If the length of the current string becomes 2*n,
it means we used all parentheses and formed a valid string.
So we add it to the result list.

Backtracking Idea:
At every step we try possible choices and explore them recursively.

add "("  if open < n
add ")"  if close < open
stop     when length == 2*n

This ensures that only valid parentheses combinations are generated.

Time Complexity:
The number of valid combinations follows Catalan numbers.

n = 1 → 1
n = 2 → 2
n = 3 → 5
n = 4 → 14
n = 5 → 42

Approximate complexity: O(4^n / √n)

One-line Summary:
Generate parentheses using backtracking, add '(' when open < n and ')' when close < open, and store the string when its length becomes 2*n.

Solved on 10/03/2026
